  <div class="col-xs-6">
    <div class="panel-custom panel-default">
      <div class="panel-heading"><h1>Website Help</h1></div>
      <div class="panel-body">
        <h3><u>Navigating around the Site</u></h3>
        <p>At the top of the page is a the Navbar which has links to all the important pages. It has the following links:
        <ul>
            <li>Home</li>
            <li>Senators</li>
            <li>General Committee and Committees</li>
            <li>Help</li>
        </ul>
        <br>
        <h4><u>Home</u></h4>
        <p>
        The Home page takes you to the home of the site. If you are a guest, it simply takes you to the login page.
        Regular users and administrators also have their respective pages.
        </p>
        <br>
        <h4><u>Senators</u></h4>
        <p>
        The Senators page shows all the senators currently stored in the system,
        as well as a link to view more details about that senator's attendance.
        </p>
        <br>
        <h4><u>General Committee and Committees</u></h4>
        <p>Both of these links take you to a committee's page. From that committee's page, you can view attendance information for that committee,
        such as attendances for specific meetings or a user's total attendances for that committee</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

