<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-6 col-sm-3">
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-6">
    <div class="panel-custom panel-default">
      <div class="panel-heading"><h2>User Actions</h2></div>
      <div class="panel-body">
        <p>As a user, you can, you can see a summary of your attendance records for each committee on the home page. You also have permission to do several other actions.</p>
        <br>
        <h4><u>Signing in to a Committee Meeting</u></h4>
        <p>To sign in to a meeting, a committee head will first start a meeting sign in. Once that has been done,
        there will be a link to sign in on that committee's page.</p>
        <br>
        <h4><u>Submitting an Excuse for an Absence</u></h4>
        <p>If you missed a meeting sign in, you can submit an excuse form. To do this, go to your home page.
        From there, click the "My Absences" link. This will take you to a list of all your absences. To submit an excuse,
        find the absence you wish to excuse, and click the "Submit Excuse" link next to the absence.
        </p>
        <h4><u>Changing your Username/Password</u></h4>
        <p>To change your username or password, click the "Change Username/Password" link on the home page.</p>
        <br>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<br>
<br>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-6 col-sm-3">
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-6">
    <div class="panel-custom panel-default">
      <div class="panel-heading"><h2>Committee Head Actions</h2></div>
      <div class="panel-body">
        <p>If you are given the role of Committee Head over a committee, you have the power to start/end committee sign ins for that committee,
         as well as approve absence excuses for that committee.</p>
        <br>
        <h4><u>Sign-In</u></h4>
         <p>
         To start a sign in, navigate to your committee's page and click "Start Meeting Sign-in".
         If no title is given, a title will be generated for you. Ending sign-in follows the same steps
         </p>
        <br>
        <h4><u>Excuses</u></h4>
         <p>
         To approve/reject excuses, click the "Committee Excuses" link, then "Edit Status" next to the excuse.
         <b>Pending and rejected excuses will count the absence as unexcused, while approved excuses will count the absence as excused.</b>
         </p>
         <p> To view users above the maximum allowed absences for the committee, click the "Users Above Max Absences" link. </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<% end %>

