      <div class="panel-heading"><h2>Admin Actions</h2></div>
      <div class="panel-body">
        <p>As an administrator, you have many powers: assigning roles to users, creating/delete users, creating/deleting committees, and adding users to
        committees.</p>
        <br>
        <h4><u>Assigning User Roles</u></h4>
        <p>To assign a user roles, click on the "Edit" link next to a user in the Senators tab. You can then edit the user's roles.</p>
        <br>
        <h4><u>Creating/Deleting Users</u></h4>
        <p>On the senators page, there are links to delete users, as well as a link at the bottom of the page to create a new user.</p>
        <br>
        <h4><u>Creating/Delete Committees</u></h4>
        <p>You can create a committee by clicking the "Create Committee" button on the user dashboard.
         You can delete a committee by going to the committee's page and clicking "Delete Committee"</p>
        <br>
        <h4><u>Adding User to a Committee</u></h4>
        <p>To add a user to a committee, navigate to the committee's page and click "Edit Committee". From here, you can add/remove users, as well as
        change the committee's name and max allowed absences of each type.</p>
